criteria.driver_alignment:
DISCOVER — student stated the problem and required outputs;  
REPRESENT — student mapped inputs/parameters and planned variables;  
IMPLEMENT — student assigned numeric inputs, computed KE, KD, weights and WACC;  
VALIDATE — student reran the model for the $3B sensitivity and reported results;  
EVOLVE — student discussed applying results to project‑level decisions.

DISCOVER — student framed the financing decision and objectives;  
IMPLEMENT — student computed baseline and post‑issuance WACCs and reported results;  
EVOLVE — student discussed implications (tax shield benefit, higher operational/financial risk) linking capital structure to firm risk.

DISCOVER — clearly stated the task and objectives;  
REPRESENT — explained the WACC formula and each component;  
IMPLEMENT/VALIDATE — walked through numeric inputs, computed KE/KD/weights, produced baseline and scenario WACCs and discussed implications.
